Authorities have recovered a body. CAPE TOWN - Police are probing the circumstances around a crash involving a light aircraft in Port Elizabeth. The plane went down earlier on Monday afternoon. Authorities have recovered a body. Police spokesperson Priscilla Naidu said: “At about 14:15 this afternoon a light aircraft crashed into the Baakens Valley in Port Elizabeth. One person was onboard the aircraft; it was just the pilot. We have recovered his body. The name of the pilot will not be released until the next of kin has been notified.” (Edited by Thapelo Lekabe)